Chairman Emeritus 
Jack Bruderman has more than a half-century of experience
in the investment business as a equity research analyst and portfolio manager. A member of the CFA Institute since 1968, he
earned an AB in economics at Georgetown University, an MBA
in finance and investments at New York University, and holds
FINRA Series 7 and 63 securities licenses.
